==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Erratum
<hw>Er*ra"tum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Errata</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr. <ets>errare</ets>,
<ets>erratum</ets>, to wander, err. See <er>Err</er>.]</ety> <def>An
error or mistake in writing or printing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A single <qex>erratum</qex> may knock out the brains of a whole
passage.</q> <rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>erring</ent>⟦br⟧
